                    <msContents>
                        <summary> The second of three incomplete volumes of the <title>Razmnāmah</title> (Book of
                            Battles) a Persian translation of the <title>Mahābhārata</title>. Translated at the behest of the
                            Mughal ruler <persName role="pat" ref="https://viaf.org/viaf/3264079" key="person_3264079">Akbar I (b. 1542, r. 1566–1605)</persName> starting in <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari" from="1582"
                                to="1583">990 AH (1582–83 CE)</date> by four
                            scholars, chiefly <persName key="person_f3120">Ibn ʿAbd al-Laṭīf Ḥusaynī
                                Naqīb-K̲h̲ān (d. ca. 1614)</persName>, as well as <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">ʻAbd al-Qādir Badāʼūnī (ca.
                                1540–1615)</persName>, <persName key="person_f2645">Muḥammad Sulṭān
                                    Thānīsārī fl. late 16th c</persName>, and <persName>Mullā S̲h̲īrī (d. ca. 1586)</persName>, to which the vizier <persName key="person_5150639">Abū
                                al-Faz̤l (1551–1602)</persName> added a preface. One of two sets
                            of this work previously held in the Chetham Library, Manchester.</summary>
                        <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_1009-item1">
                            <author role="ant" key="person_7739151778235418130004" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/7739151778235418130004">
                                <persName type="standard">Vyāsa</persName>; <lb/>
                                <persName xml:lang="sa">ব্যাস, কৃষ্ণদ্বৈপায়ণ</persName>
                            </author>
                            <author role="trl" key="person_f3120"><persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f3120">Ibn ʿAbd
                                al-Laṭīf Ḥusaynī Naqīb-K̲h̲ān (d. 1614)</persName>; <lb/>
                                <persName xml:lang="fa">ابن عبد اللطیف نقیب خان</persName></author>
                            <author role="trl" ref="https://viaf.org/viaf/57046582/"
                                key="person_57046582">
                                <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Badāʼūnī, ʻAbd al-Qādir ibn Mulūk
                                    Shāh, ca. 1540–1615</persName>; <lb/>
                                <persName xml:lang="fa">عبد القادر بن ملوكشاه بدائونی</persName>
                            </author>
                            <author role="trl" key="person_f2645">
                                <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Muḥammad Sulṭān
                                    Thānīsārī, fl. late 16th c.</persName>; <lb/>
                                <persName xml:lang="fa">محمد سلطان ثانیساری</persName>
                            </author>
                            <author role="trl" key="person_f7936">
                                <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Mullā Shīrī, d. ca. 1586</persName>; <lb/>
                                <persName xml:lang="fa">ملا شیری</persName>
                            </author>
                            <author role="aui wpr" key="person_5150639">
                                <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Abū al-Faz̤l ibn
                                    Mubārak, 1551-1602</persName>
                                <persName xml:lang="fa">ابو الفضل بن مبارك</persName>
                            </author>
                            <editor role="pat" ref="https://viaf.org/viaf/3264079" key="person_3264079">
                                <persName>Akbar, Emperor of Hindustan, b. 1542, r. 1566–1605</persName>
                            </editor>
                            <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_9117">Razmnāmah</title>
                            <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_9117">رزمنامه</title>
                            <title xml:lang="sa-Latn-x-lc" type="alt" key="work_9117"
                                >Mahābhārata</title>
                            <title xml:lang="sa" key="work_9117">महाभारतम्</title>
                            <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_9117">مهابهارته</title>
                            <title type="desc" xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_9117">Persian
                                translation of the Mahābhārata</title>
                            <title type="desc" xml:lang="fa" key="work_8497">ترجمه‌ٔ
                                هابهارته</title>
                            <incipit>
                                <locus from="1b" to="1b"> برگ ۱پ (folio 1b):</locus> ای هژده هزار
                                عالم از شوق تو مست * سر در سر جست و جوی جان بر کف دست. </incipit>
                            <explicit/>
                            <colophon/>
                            <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                            <note>For another three-volume set of this work held in the Rylands, see
                                    <ref
                                    target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_26523"
                                        ><idno>Persian MS 1004</idno></ref> to <ref
                                    target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_26528"
                                    >1007</ref>. For another ornate prose redaction based upon this
                                version by Abū al-Faz̤l's brother, the poet <persName
                                    key="person_90041360">Fayz̤ī (d. 1595)</persName> in two
                                volumes, see <ref
                                    target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_7343"
                                        ><idno>Persian MS 835</idno></ref> and <ref
                                    target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_7344"
                                    >836</ref>.</note>
                        </msItem>
